{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1513821819,"nonce":"G0pALG3iooqp0Ht1U/a+Fwr908g=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyODM3NTEwNjA=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1644","origin":"github"},"title":"Mothur Make.biom does not recognize tabular datatype dataset as \"metadata\" input","message":"Make.biom (version 1.36.1.0)\nhttps://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/view/iuc/mothur_make_biom/5dc4d49a238a\n\nDataset 10 in this test history is an example of proper tabular input for the \"metadata\" tool form options, but it cannot be selected: https://galaxy.uni-freiburg.de/u/jenj/h/test-history-mothur-subsample\n\nTrue also at https://usegalaxy.org, so either a problem with the tool wrapper or Galaxy itself (v17.09). If not the tool, we can move this over to the /galaxy repo. The other two primary inputs capture appropriate input dataset fine.\n\nUsed in the [16S metagenomics GTN tutorial](http://galaxyproject.github.io/training-material/topics/metagenomics/tutorials/mothur-miseq-sop/tutorial.html), step 'Hands-on: Phinch\"\n\nfrom `make.biom.xml`\n```\n \u003cinputs\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"otu\" type=\"data\" format=\"mothur.shared\" label=\"shared - OTU Shared file\"/\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"constaxonomy\" type=\"data\" format=\"mothur.cons.taxonomy\" optional=\"true\" label=\"contaxonomy - consensus taxonomy\" help=\"The contaxonomy file is the taxonomy file outputted by classify.otu\"/\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"metadata\" type=\"data\" format=\"tabular\" label=\"metadata\" optional=\"true\" help=\"You can add sample data support here\"/\u003e\n```","files":null}]}